                  </persName>
            . I am an officer, and conveyed Wyeth and the prisoner to prison; as they were going along, Steers said to Wyeth, "This fellow has sworn false, and if he swears up yonder (meaning here), he will top us- he said this b - l - y foolish thing - "<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182802210047"></xptr>Prisoner's Defence. I am brought here to be sold by Mr. Cook; he is bribed to do it.</p>

               <p>GUILTY. Aged 25.</p>
